MIS 311 Assignment #1: Supermarket Sales Analysis
Part 1: Data Analysis and Insight Generation

This project performs Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on a Supermarket Sales dataset.
The purpose is to understand the structure of the data, prepare it for analysis, and identify meaningful insights related to supermarket sales performance.

1. Data Overview

The selected dataset is the Supermarket Sales dataset, which was provided as part of the MIS 311 Assignment #1 materials. It contains information about supermarket sales transactions, including sales ID, branch, city, customer type, product name, product category, quantity sold, and total sales price.

The original dataset includes 253 rows and 8 columns, where each row represents one sales transaction. This dataset is suitable for exploratory data analysis because it allows us to examine how sales performance differs by city and product category.

Main Groups of Variables
