The missing value check shows that missing values were found in customer_type, product_category, and quantity. Since the number of missing values was small, incomplete rows were removed to keep the analysis accurate.

2.2 Checking for Duplicate Rows

The dataset was checked for duplicate rows using Excel’s Remove Duplicates function.

The dataset contained 3 duplicated rows. These duplicate rows were removed before analysis to ensure that each sales transaction was counted only once.

2.3 Data Cleaning Summary

Overall, the dataset required basic cleaning before analysis. The original dataset contained 253 rows and 8 columns. After removing 3 duplicate rows and incomplete records with missing values, the final cleaned dataset contained 239 complete rows.

This cleaned dataset was then used for descriptive statistics, pivot tables, visualisations, and insight generation.

3. Descriptive Statistics and Insight Generation

After confirming that the dataset was cleaned and ready for analysis, descriptive statistics were used to summarise the main characteristics of the data. The analysis focuses on identifying meaningful patterns related to supermarket sales performance and supporting these findings with appropriate visualisations.

