Key Insight 2: Fruits Had the Highest Revenue Among Product Categories

Fruits generated the highest total revenue, with total sales of 7,450.12 USD, followed by Beverages and Stationery. This indicates that Fruits contributed the most to supermarket revenue among all product categories. The supermarket should maintain sufficient stock for Fruits and consider suitable promotions to further increase sales in this category.

4. Conclusion

This exploratory data analysis examined the Supermarket Sales dataset to understand its structure, check data quality, and identify meaningful sales patterns. The dataset required basic cleaning because it contained missing values and duplicate rows. After cleaning, the final dataset contained 239 complete records and was suitable for further analysis.

Two key findings were identified. First, Chicago generated the highest total revenue, followed closely by New York. Second, Fruits generated the highest revenue among all product categories. Overall, these findings suggest that sales performance differs across cities and product categories, which can support better marketing, inventory, and sales planning decisions.
